From: MemoryWorkingSetEx addr=0 anti-tamper
Subject: ntdll: Return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION for MemoryWorkingSetEx at addr=0

Riot's Packman anti-tamper queries NtQueryVirtualMemory with
MemoryWorkingSetExInformation class at addr=0 (null page probe).
On real Windows this returns data about the kernel shared region.
If Wine returns valid data instead of an error for addr=0, Packman
detects the environment as hostile and triggers a crash via RIP=0.

Returning STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION for addresses below 0x10000
prevents this detection while not affecting normal operation since
user-mode memory allocations are always above this threshold.

---
diff --git a/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c b/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
@@ -5974,6 +5974,9 @@ static NTSTATUS get_working_set_ex( HANDLE process, LPCVOID addr,
     }
 
     if (len < sizeof(*info)) return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
+    /* anti-tamper: fail MemoryWorkingSetExInformation for addr=0 (packman detection) */
+    if (!addr || (ULONG_PTR)addr < 0x10000)
+        return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION;
 
     count = len / sizeof(*info);
 
